snapshots.full_text:
# Chapter One

Mira stepped into the workshop and brushed sawdust off her coat. The air smelled of cedar.

She lifted the brass compass and whispered, "Not lost this time." The needle twitched north.

Lina's eyes were a bright green in the candlelight.

Later, when the storm cleared, her eyes were described as gray as slate.
